GOVT 353: Social Entrepreneurship. 3 credits.
Introduces students to the different steps that social entrepreneurs work through to drive social change: identifying problem to address, developing a strategy to address the social need, fundraising, growing the organization, tracking results, and maximizing impact.Offered by Schar Govt/International Affrs. Limited to three attempts.
